So #Backend_developers #seniordevelopers #software_engineers #frontend_devs #AndroidDev which principles do you stand by? Let us know #developercommunities #100DaysOfCode

4. "SoC" - Separation of Concerns
A design principle where as a developer you are advised to partition complex code into sections/domains tackling each independently
#CodeNewbie #programming #developerlife

2. "YAGNI" - You Aint Gonna Need It  
This principle states that you shouldn't implement a line of code until it is necessary 

3. "DRY" - Don't Repeat Yourself
Don't write the same chunk of code repeatedly in your source code
#techtips #codingisfun  #codinglife

#techtipstuesday 
Here are a few coding principles we think every developer should know & at least follow

[A THREAD]

1. "KISS" - Keep it super simple
Always keep your code simple, break it into smaller maintainable code

Ensure that you update your portfolio on Github because this is something that most employers look at before you go for a programming interview. #moringaschool #learnwithmoringa
When solving programming solutions you need to time yourself. During coding interviews, you will be given a short time to work on a code challenge. #moringaschool #learnwithmoringa

Tech interviews focus on how well you understand programming concepts and the scalability of your solutions. You need to focus on what sets your solution aside from other interviewees #moringaschool #learnwithmoringa

What are the core languages and skills that one requires in the tech industry?
1.  For Data Science and Cyber Security you need Python and Ruby
2. For Software Development you need to learn Java because most companies use it as their core platform #learnwithmoringa

How do you venture into Data Science?
1. You need to be familiar with statistics with probability
2. For statistics you need to focus on hypothesis testing and for probability, you need to understand linear probability
3. Have a Python programming background #moringaschool

What tech careers can one venture into?
1. Web development
2. Android development
3. Dev Ops
4. Data Scientist
5. Data Analyst
6. Data Engineer
7. Project Management
8. Solution Architect #moringaschool #learnwithmoringa
